There's gonna be people who shame me, hate on me and any who list for floor / below pre reveal. My only advice is have conviction for your choice, get a good reason, and ignore them. Don't worry if it turns out rare, if floor moons you did what was right on the knowledge you had

I instantly paid back EVERYONE who gave me the eth and continue to look into flipping the eth I have. With such a small amount It's necessary to flip early and take small profit I don't have a safety net of ETH incase a long term hold goes to 0

but It was a start with my very small eth left over ~.19 I had 2 other people be generous and give me money to try and cover any gas fees, I got MegaPal for wonderpals and minted 2! I then sold one for 1eth an insane flip for most people and especially right off the bat.

I'd run the server, I got lot's of inspiration from the Cool Cats discord and the people I met, I then get Whitelist for a project and someone offers me some funds, the next day the SAME thing offers me WL and the funds to mint (Both under minting price now rip)

We set up a meeting so I could meet @0xVinasaur and @velvetmooncake the Dev and Artist on the team.... And I missed the meeting. Completely got busy and forgot go first job right? Luckily they were super forgiving. I started thinking immediately, giving ideas, and wondering how

a project he was working on, I didn't know any details but we introduced ourselves and went on our way, flash forward to late Nov/early Dec I reached back out just to have an update on where we were for the project and we talked a bit and got into the discord early December

Back in October I put a looking for work in the cool cats discord for a CM position unpaid, I'm a teenager and have no experience. I said I didn't want to be paid because the learning and experience would be enough @JensenTung reached out within 24 hours letting me know about

Threw a curveball my way, ALL pet nominees were on the WL I immediately messaged her (Uncle Frex) on discord and asked if I could submit someone else's wallet and that's the end of that story. Now onto my journey of earning ETH.

I didn't have ETH and didn't have a way to get eth. I don't like handouts or asking for money (Especially that much) so I asked for my nomination to be given to someone else, he kindly said it was probably gonna be a raffle so I told myself I just wouldn't enter then @lilfrecklez

.@Grampa_Bacon and @ItsTymo when I first got nominated by Adam I was super stoked it felt good to be recognized especially as a kid in a space full of tech wizards, finance magicians, and all the above. I looked at that nomination and was super happy there was just one issue...

as I 17 year old with no bank account all the NFT's (Airdrops) I had, I had earned, not out of pocket etc. Even if I lost EVERYTHING I would be content that I hadn't gone negative and lost money . Fast forward to cool pets, as many of you know I was nominated by...

S/O to Ali (Liam) for putting up with me wondering how to turn weth into eth without needing to have gas funds so I could mint @VinnieHager's letters i got WL for (Sadly I missed mint), I went into this space knowing i'd lose money there was a glimmer of hope though

I met so many amazing people one of the first being @officialalim, I hung out in the cool cats discord so often and continued to see the positivity and enjoy being there. I continued to learn and ask questions about this space and asked for a LOT of direction and advice

I first found out about NFT's because @frak5555 asked @Yasin_Wunsung for help on @coolcatsnft very first puzzle. Me and Yasin (Sensei) made puzzles together online from other discords so he made a GC and brought me in, from there we solved the puzzle "Cats Hodl/hold for life.....
Here's my journey 1/x? (hopefully short)
